  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of safe water for 700 inhabitants</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">About 700 inhabitants in the Mudagammana village in Kandy district in Sri Lanka  face acute shortage of clean water for drinking and domestic purposes. This water shortage has an impact on the well being and economic activities of the community leading to poor sanitation and recurrent health problems. In this project, we propose to construct a sustainable s water supply system to bring down water through gravity from a perennial water stream located at higher elevation.</narrative>
  </description>
